===Royal Air Force===
All four engined ''heavies'' operated from Wideawake Airfield, [[Ascension Island]], but flew in the war zone.

* [[No. 1 Squadron RAF|No. 1(F) Squadron]] - ([[Hawker Siddeley Harrier|Harrier GR.3]]) '''10 (4)''' ''([[HMS Hermes (R12)|HMS Hermes]] & Port San Carlos)''
* [[No. 18 Squadron RAF|No. 18 Squadron]] - ([[CH-47 Chinook|Chinook HC.1]]) '''4 (3)''' ''+1 at Wideawake''
* [[No. 29 Squadron RAF|No. 29 Squadron]] - ([[F-4 Phantom|Phantom FGR.2]]) '''3'''; ''only at Wideawake''
* [[No. 39 Squadron RAF|No. 39 Squadron]] - ([[English Electric Canberra|Canberra PR.9]]) '''2'''; ''Clandestine operations from Chile''<ref>http://www.britains-smallwars.com/Falklands/aircraft.html#canberra</ref><ref>http://www.raf.mod.uk/falklands/rafau.html</ref>
* [[No. 42 Squadron RAF|No. 42 Squadron]] - ([[Hawker-Siddeley Nimrod|Nimrod MR.2]]) <sub>13 MR.2 from all squadrons</sub>
* [[No. 44 Squadron RAF|No. 44 Squadron]] - ([[Avro Vulcan|Vulcan B.2]]) '''2'''
* [[No. 47 Squadron RAF|No. 47 Squadron]] - ([[C-130 Hercules|Hercules C.1]])
* [[No. 50 Squadron RAF|No. 50 Squadron]] - ([[Avro Vulcan|Vulcan B.2]]) '''1'''
* [[No. 51 Squadron RAF|No. 51 Squadron]] - ([[Hawker-Siddeley Nimrod|Nimrod R.1]]) '''3'''
* [[No. 55 Squadron RAF|No. 55 Squadron]] - ([[Handley Page Victor|Victor K.2]]) <sub>20 Victor K.2 from both squadrons</sub>
* [[No. 57 Squadron RAF|No. 57 Squadron]] - ([[Handley Page Victor|Victor K.2]])
* [[No. 70 Squadron RAF|No. 70 Squadron]] - ([[C-130 Hercules|Hercules C.1]])
* [[No. 101 Squadron RAF|No. 101 Squadron]] - ([[Avro Vulcan|Vulcan B.2]]) '''1'''
* [[No. 120 Squadron RAF|No. 120 Squadron]] - ([[Hawker-Siddeley Nimrod|Nimrod MR.2]])
* [[No. 201 Squadron RAF|No. 201 Squadron]] - ([[Hawker-Siddeley Nimrod|Nimrod MR.2]])
* [[No. 202 Squadron RAF|No. 202 Squadron]] - ([[Westland Sea King|Sea King HAR.3]]) '''1'''  ''only at Wideawake''
* [[No. 206 Squadron RAF|No. 206 Squadron]] - ([[Hawker-Siddeley Nimrod|Nimrod MR.2]])

===Armament===

* [[L7 (machine gun)|L44A1 GPMG (General Purpose Machine Gun)]]
* [[ADEN cannon|30 mm ADEN Cannon]] with 120-130 rounds ''Sea Harrier, Harrier GR.3''
* [[AIM-9 Sidewinder|AIM-9D/G Sidewinder]] [[Air-to-air missile]] (AAM) ''F-4 at Wideawake''
* [[AIM-9 Sidewinder|AIM-9L Sidewinder]] AAM ''Sea Harrier, Harrier GR.3'' <ref>[http://www.f-16.net/f-16_armament_article1.html AIM-9L Sidewinder air kills]</ref>
* [[AGM-45 Shrike]] [[Air-to-surface missile|Air-to-Surface]] [[Anti-radiation missile|Anti-radiation missile (ARM)]] ''Vulcan''
* [[Sea Skua|BAe Sea Skua]] Air-to-Surface [[anti-ship missile]] ''Lynx''
* [[Aerospatiale SS.12/AS.12|Aerospatiale AS.12]] Air-to-Surface missile ''Wasp''
* [[Paveway]] II [[Laser-guided bomb]] (LGB), 454&nbsp;kg ''Harrier GR.3''
* [[BL755]] [[Cluster bomb]] with 147 bomblets  ''Sea Harrier''
* 1,000&nbsp;lb [[General-purpose bomb|General Purpose Bomb]] ''Sea Harrier, Harrier GR.3 & Vulcan''
* [[SNEB]] Rockets ''Harrier GR.3, Gazelle''<ref>
{{cite book|url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ZUjMYkfr-pwC&pg=PA14&lpg=PA14&dq=gazelle+sneb&source=bl&ots=MCopeM2epk&sig=EZdrjTULU-68K144evK2VEFz3Rw&hl=en&ei=JsLFSobAMuO6jAf6yoFN&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1#v=onepage&q=sneb&f=false|title=Battle for the Falklands (3): Air Forces - Google Books|publisher=books.google.co.uk|accessdate=2009-10-02}}</ref>
* [[Mark 46 torpedo|Mk. 46 Torpedo]]
* Mk. 11 [[Depth charge]]

==Air Campaign==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Sea Harrier FRS.1
| 1,435 sorties,<ref>[http://www.britains-smallwars.com/Falklands/air-war.htm Falklands Air War<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> 20 (+3) kills, 6 lost. 
|-
| Harrier GR.3
| 126 sorties, 4 lost. 
|-
| Vulcan B.2
| [[Operation Black Buck|5 sorties]]: 1, 3 May and 12 June; 21x1,000&nbsp;lbs bombs - 31 May and 3 June; 4<ref>"armed with four Shrikes for another attack against the Falklands." page 67 in Peter R. March: The Vulcan Story, 2006, Sutton Publishing/'Vulcan to the Sky' trust, ISBN 0-7509-4399-8</ref> x[[AGM-45 Shrike]]. 
|-
| Victor K.2
| 375 sorties; 14 sorties per Vulcan raid, 12 sorties per extended Nimrod patrol, 6 sorties per Hercules long-range drop, 6 sorties per Harrier GR.3 staging (4), 3 radar reconnaissance sorties to South Georgia.
|-
| Nimrod MR.2
| 111 sorties: maritime patrols, coordinate air refueling, SAR links.  
|-
| Hercules C.1
| 50+ airdrop sorties at Falklands Island, 600+ airbridge sorties UK-Ascension Island
|}

==Casualties and aircraft losses==

* '''Human losses''':
** 2 [[Army Air Corps (United Kingdom)|Army Air Corps]]<ref name=Gaz6Jun>[[1982 British Army Gazelle friendly fire incident]]: [[A<U+00E9>rospatiale Gazelle|Gazelle]] shot down by friendly [[Sea Dart missile]] from [[HMS Cardiff (D108)|HMS Cardiff]] on 6 June. All four onboard killed, two from [[No. 656 Squadron AAC|656 Squadron]], [[Army Air Corps (United Kingdom)|Army Air Corps]] and two from [[205 Signal Squadron]], [[Royal Corps of Signals]]</ref>
** 4 [[3 Commando Brigade Air Squadron]] Royal Marines
** 17 [[Fleet Air Arm]]
* '''Passengers'''
** 1 [[Royal Air Force]]<ref name="19may92">[http://www.britains-smallwars.com/Falklands/brit-aircraftlosses.htm] Probable bird strike to transport helicopter operating between ''Intrepid'' and ''Hermes'' on 20 May</ref>
** 18 [[Special Air Service]] ([[British Army|Army]])<ref name="19may92"/>
** 3  [[Royal Corps of Signals]] (Army)<ref name =Gaz6Jun/><ref name="19may92"/>

* '''Aircraft Lost in the Air''':, <sub>no suffix: ''Fleet Air Arm''</sub>
** 2 [[Sea Harrier|Sea Harrier FRS.1]] (hit by anti-aircraft fire during 4 May attack on Goose Green and by [[Roland missile]] during 1 June attack on Port Stanley)<ref name="e&p">Ethell, Jeffrey and Price, Alfred ''Air War South Atlantic'' Macmillan Publishing Company (1983) pp.248-251 ISBN 0-02-536300-X</ref>
** 3 [[Westland Gazelle|Westland Gazelle AH.1]] ''Army'' and ''Royal Marines''<ref name=Gaz6Jun/><ref name="21may92">[http://www.britains-smallwars.com/Falklands/brit-aircraftlosses.htm] (2 Gazelles shot down by Argentine army forces small arms leaving San Carlos area on 21 May)</ref>
** 3 [[Hawker Siddeley Harrier|Harrier GR.3]] ''RAF'' (shot down by [[shoulder-fired missile]] in [[Port Howard]] on 21 May, hit by anti-aircraft fire on 27 May over Goose Green and hit by ground fire near Port Stanley on 30 May)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 1 [[Westland Scout|Scout AH.1]] ''Royal Marines'' (shot down by Pucara at Goose Green on 28 May)<ref name="e&p"/>

* '''Flying accidents in the war zone'''
** 2 [[Westland Wessex|Westland Wessex HU.5]] (crashed on in bad weather on Fortune Glacier 22 April)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 2 [[Westland Sea King|Westland Sea King HC.4]]<ref name="19may92"/> (1 lost operational accident 23 April)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 4 Sea Harrier FRS.1 (two 801 Sqn CAP collided over the task force on 6 May - one 800 Sqn crashed during takeoff from ''Hermes'' on 24 May - one 801 Sqn slid off deck in bad weather on 29 May)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 2 Westland Sea King HAS.5 (ditched on 12 May & 17 May)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 1 Harrier GR.3 ''RAF'' (landing accident on 8 June)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 1 [[Westland Scout|Scout AH.1]] ''Royal Marines'' (crash landed after main rotor gearbox failure over MacPhee Pond, 8 June. Recovered but wrtitten off.)<ref name="e&p"/>
* '''Lost on board a ship'''
** 3 [[Westland Lynx|Westland Lynx HAS.2]] (aboard ''Ardent'' on 21 May and aboard ''Coventry'' and ''Atlantic Conveyor'' on 25 May)<ref name="e&p"/>
** 3 [[CH-47 Chinook|Chinook HC.1]] ''RAF''<ref name="AtCon">25 May aboard ''Atlantic Conveyor''</ref>
** 6 Westland Wessex HU.5<ref name="AtCon"/>
** 1 Westland Wessex HAS.3 (when ''Glamorgan'' hit by shore-launched Exocet on 12 June)<ref name="e&p"/>

* '''Self-destruct in Chile'''
** 1 [[Westland Sea King|Westland Sea King HC.4]] (on 20 May)<ref name="e&p"/>

